{"url": "https://www.goodreads.com/book/show/2442.Witches_Abroad", "title": "Witches Abroad", "titleComplete": "Witches Abroad (Discworld, #12; Witches, #3)", "description": "Be careful what you wish for...Once upon a time there was a fairy godmother named Desiderata who had a good heart, a wise head, and poor planning skills\u2014which unfortunately left the Princess Emberella in the care of her other (not quite so good and wise) godmother when DEATH came for Desiderata. So now it's up to Magrat Garlick, Granny Weatherwax, and Nanny Ogg to hop on broomsticks and make for far-distant Genua to ensure the servant girl doesn't marry the Prince.But the road to Genua is bumpy, and along the way the trio of witches encounters the occasional vampire, werewolf, and falling house (well this is a fairy tale, after all). The trouble really begins once these reluctant foster-godmothers arrive in Genua and must outwit their power-hungry counterpart who'll stop at nothing to achieve a proper \"happy ending\"\u2014even if it means destroying a kingdom.", "imageUrl": "https://images-na.ssl-images-amazon.com/images/S/compressed.photo.goodreads.com/books/1403326937i/2442.jpg", "genres": ["Science Fiction Fantasy", "Comedy", "Fantasy", "Witches", "Audiobook", "Magic", "High Fantasy", "Humor", "Fiction", "Adventure"], "asin": "0061020613", "isbn": "0061020613", "isbn13": "9780061020612", "publisher": "Harper", "series": ["Kolekcja \u015awiat Dysku", "Wielka Kolekcja Terry Pratchett", "Discworld - Witches", "Discworld"], "author": ["Terry Pratchett"], "publishDate": 1028012400000, "characters": ["Granny Weatherwax", "Greebo", "Lily Weatherwax", "Nanny Ogg", "DEATH", "Mrs. Gogol", "Magrat Garlick"], "places": ["Genua, Discworld", "Discworld"], "ratingHistogram": [555, 1836, 13348, 32308, 40617], "ratingsCount": 88664, "reviewsCount": 3024, "numPages": 374, "language": "English"}
{"url": "https://www.goodreads.com/book/show/47345.Man_and_Boy", "title": "Man and Boy", "titleComplete": "Man and Boy (Harry Silver, #1)", "description": "HE HAD TO FACE THE TOUGHEST JOB OF HIS LIFE. AND HE NEVER ONCE THOUGHT HE'D BE ON HIS OWN.Harry had it a beautiful wife, an adorable four-year-old son, and a high-paying media job. But on the eve of his thirtieth birthday, with one irresponsible act, he threw it all away. Suddenly he finds himself an unemployed single father trying to figure out how to wash his son's hair the way Mommy did and whether green spaghetti is proper breakfast food. This brilliantly engaging novel will tug at your heart as Harry learns to become a father to his son and a son to his aging father, takes stabs at finding new love, and makes the hardest decision of his life.", "imageUrl": "https://images-na.ssl-images-amazon.com/images/S/compressed.photo.goodreads.com/books/1388877591i/47345.jpg", "genres": ["Contemporary", "Novels", "Drama", "Humor", "Family", "Chick Lit", "Adult", "Fiction", "Romance", "British Literature"], "asin": "0743225082", "isbn": "0743225082", "isbn13": "9780743225083", "publisher": "Touchstone", "series": ["Harry Silver"], "author": ["Tony Parsons"], "publishDate": 1020754800000, "characters": ["Harry Silver"], "ratingHistogram": [463, 1531, 5568, 5953, 2991], "ratingsCount": 16506, "reviewsCount": 798, "numPages": 361, "language": "English", "awards": [{"name": "British Book Award", "awardedAt": 978336000000, "category": null, "hasWon": null}]}
