{"url": "https://www.goodreads.com/book/show/122.The_Power_of_One", "title": "The Power of One", "titleComplete": "The Power of One (The Power of One, #1)", "description": "In 1939, as Hitler casts his enormous, cruel shadow across the world, the seeds of apartheid take root in South Africa. There, a boy called Peekay is born. His childhood is marked by humiliation and abandonment, yet he vows to survive and conceives heroic dreams, which are nothing compared to what life actually has in store for him. He embarks on an epic journey through a land of tribal superstition and modern prejudice where he will learn the power of words, the power to transform lives and the power of one.", "imageUrl": "https://images-na.ssl-images-amazon.com/images/S/compressed.photo.goodreads.com/books/1388184360i/122.jpg", "genres": ["Classics", "Novels", "Young Adult", "South Africa", "Literature", "Historical", "Historical Fiction", "Africa", "Coming Of Age", "Fiction"], "asin": "034541005X", "isbn": "034541005X", "isbn13": "9780345410054", "publisher": "Ballantine Books", "series": ["The Power of One"], "author": ["Bryce Courtenay"], "publishDate": 843980400000, "characters": ["Peekay", "Geel Piet", "\"Doc\" Bradley Stanwick", "Miss Bornstein", "Mrs. Boxall", "Morris Levy", "The Judge"], "places": ["South Africa"], "ratingHistogram": [1223, 2417, 9512, 26465, 48992], "ratingsCount": 88609, "reviewsCount": 5893, "numPages": 544, "language": "English", "awards": [{"name": "West Australian Young Readers' Book Award (WAYRBA)", "awardedAt": 820483200000, "category": "Older Readers", "hasWon": null}]}
