{"url": "https://www.goodreads.com/book/show/511566.The_Suitcase_Kid", "title": "The Suitcase Kid", "titleComplete": "The Suitcase Kid", "description": "Andrea West\u2019s parents are divorced, and her tiny stuffed rabbit, Radish, seems her only comfort in the world. She must leave the home she loves with the mulberry tree in the front yard and deal with parents who still fight, stepparents, step-siblings, two different bedrooms (neither of which is really hers), loneliness, and an acute longing for the past. Her grades sink, her friends drift away, and she's not quite sure how to fix any of it. Eventually, though, a new equilibrium begins to settle on her life. Honest and true-to-life, Andy\u2019s story shows that dealing with divorce is never easy.", "imageUrl": "https://images-na.ssl-images-amazon.com/images/S/compressed.photo.goodreads.com/books/1353573578i/511566.jpg", "genres": ["Contemporary", "Middle Grade", "Divorce", "Childrens", "Novels", "Young Adult", "School", "Family", "Fiction", "Realistic Fiction"], "asin": "0440867738", "isbn": "0440867738", "isbn13": "9780440867739", "publisher": "Transworld Publishers", "author": ["Jacqueline Wilson", "Nick Sharratt"], "publishDate": 1191567600000, "ratingHistogram": [322, 1236, 3825, 3732, 3351], "ratingsCount": 12466, "reviewsCount": 451, "numPages": 160, "language": "English"}
{"url": "https://www.goodreads.com/book/show/71728.Jonathan_Livingston_Seagull", "title": "Jonathan Livingston Seagull", "titleComplete": "Jonathan Livingston Seagull", "description": "This is a story for people who follow their hearts and make their own rules...people who get special pleasure out of doing something well, even if only for themselves...people who know there's more to this living than meets the eye: they\u2019ll be right there with Jonathan, flying higher and faster than ever they dreamed.Jonathan Livingston Seagull is no ordinary bird. He believes it is every gull's right to fly, to reach the ultimate freedom of challenge and discovery, finding his greatest reward in teaching younger gulls the joy of flight and the power of dreams. The special 20th anniversary release of this spiritual classic!", "imageUrl": "https://images-na.ssl-images-amazon.com/images/S/compressed.photo.goodreads.com/books/1432222358i/71728.jpg", "genres": ["Classics", "Novels", "Fantasy", "Philosophy", "Inspirational", "Self Help", "Literature", "Spirituality", "Fiction", "Animals"], "asin": "0743278909", "isbn": "0743278909", "isbn13": "9780743278904", "publisher": "Scribner", "author": ["Russell Munson", "Richard Bach"], "publishDate": 1139299200000, "characters": ["Fletcher Lynd Seagull", "Chiang", "Jonathan Livingston Seagull"], "ratingHistogram": [8956, 20796, 56488, 75390, 88776], "ratingsCount": 250406, "reviewsCount": 10898, "numPages": 112, "language": "English", "awards": [{"name": "Nene Award", "awardedAt": 126259200000, "category": null, "hasWon": null}]}
{"url": "https://www.goodreads.com/book/show/157993.The_Little_Prince", "title": "The Little Prince", "titleComplete": "The Little Prince", "description": "A pilot stranded in the desert awakes one morning to see, standing before him, the most extraordinary little fellow. \"Please,\" asks the stranger, \"draw me a sheep.\" And the pilot realizes that when life's events are too difficult to understand, there is no choice but to succumb to their mysteries. He pulls out pencil and paper... And thus begins this wise and enchanting fable that, in teaching the secret of what is really important in life, has changed forever the world for its readers.Few stories are as widely read and as universally cherished by children and adults alike as The Little Prince, presented here in a stunning new translation with carefully restored artwork. The definitive edition of a worldwide classic, it will capture the hearts of readers of all ages.", "imageUrl": "https://images-na.ssl-images-amazon.com/images/S/compressed.photo.goodreads.com/books/1367545443i/157993.jpg", "genres": ["Middle Grade", "French Literature", "Childrens", "France", "Novels", "Fantasy", "Young Adult", "School", "Philosophy", "Literature"], "publisher": "Harcourt, Inc.", "author": ["Richard Howard", "Antoine de Saint-Exup\u00e9ry"], "publishDate": 962262000000, "places": ["Sahara Desert"], "ratingHistogram": [35830, 73345, 256459, 540176, 1188818], "ratingsCount": 2094628, "reviewsCount": 66936, "numPages": 96, "language": "English", "awards": [{"name": "Retro Hugo Award", "awardedAt": 1546329600000, "category": "Best Novella", "hasWon": null}]}
