{"url": "https://www.goodreads.com/book/show/853374.Secrets", "title": "Secrets", "titleComplete": "Secrets", "description": "India lives in a large, luxurious house with a mum she can't stand and a dad she adores, though he hasn't had much time for her recently. She seeks solace in her journal, which she keeps in sincere imitation of her heroine, Anne Frank. Treasure lives on the local council estate with her loving and capable grandmother. She is devoted to her nan but lives in fear of having to go back to live with her mother and violent stepfather.A chance meeting sparks a great friendship between the girls. And when Treasure has to run away to avoid her stepfather, India comes up with a hiding place inspired by her favourite writer. India hasn't got a real secret annexe like Anne Frank - but she has got a hidden attic . . .", "imageUrl": "https://images-na.ssl-images-amazon.com/images/S/compressed.photo.goodreads.com/books/1178915507i/853374.jpg", "genres": ["Contemporary", "Middle Grade", "Childrens", "Novels", "Young Adult", "Family", "Teen", "Fiction", "British Literature", "Realistic Fiction"], "asin": "0440865085", "isbn": "0440865085", "isbn13": "9780440865087", "publisher": "Corgi", "author": ["Jacqueline Wilson"], "publishDate": 1054018800000, "ratingHistogram": [170, 633, 2130, 1978, 1547], "ratingsCount": 6458, "reviewsCount": 214, "numPages": 220, "language": "English"}
{"url": "https://www.goodreads.com/book/show/48002.Thief_of_Time", "title": "Thief of Time", "titleComplete": "Thief of Time (Discworld, #26; Death, #5)", "description": "Time is a resource. Everyone knows it has to be managed.And on the Discworld that is the job of the Monks of History, who store it and pump it from the places where it's wasted (like underwater - how much time does a codfish need?) to places like cities, where there's never enough time.But the construction of the world's first truly accurate clock starts a race against, well, time for Lu Tze and his apprentice Lobsang Ludd. Because it will stop time. And that will only be the start of everyone's problems.\"Thief of Time\" comes complete with a full supporting cast of heroes, villains, yetis, martial artists and Ronnie, the fifth Horseman of the Apocalypse (who left before they became famous).", "imageUrl": "https://images-na.ssl-images-amazon.com/images/S/compressed.photo.goodreads.com/books/1388177603i/48002.jpg", "genres": ["Novels", "Science Fiction Fantasy", "Science Fiction", "Comedy", "Fantasy", "Audiobook", "Time Travel", "High Fantasy", "Humor", "Fiction"], "asin": "0061031321", "isbn": "0061031321", "isbn13": "9780061031328", "publisher": "HarperTorch", "series": ["Kolekcja \u015awiat Dysku", "Death", "Discworld"], "author": ["Terry Pratchett"], "publishDate": 1199174400000, "characters": ["Monks of History", "Death of Rats", "Nanny Ogg", "DEATH", "The Four Horsemen of the Apocalypse", "The Auditors", "Lu-Tze", "Susan Sto Helit", "Ronny Soak"], "places": ["Ankh-Morpork"], "ratingHistogram": [497, 1420, 9932, 25883, 33710], "ratingsCount": 71442, "reviewsCount": 2178, "numPages": 378, "language": "English", "awards": [{"name": "Locus Award", "awardedAt": 1009872000000, "category": null, "hasWon": null}, {"name": "Bollinger Everyman Wodehouse Prize", "awardedAt": 1009872000000, "category": "Comic Fiction", "hasWon": null}]}
{"url": "https://www.goodreads.com/book/show/63720.The_Fifth_Elephant", "title": "The Fifth Elephant", "titleComplete": "The Fifth Elephant (Discworld, #24; City Watch, #5)", "description": "Sam Vimes is a man on the run.Yesterday he was a duke, a chief of police and the ambassador to the mysterious, fat-rich country of Uberworld.Now he was nothing but his native wit and the gloomy trousers of Uncle Vanya (don't ask). It's snowing. It's freezing. And if he can't make it through the forest to civilisation there's going to be a terrible war.But there are monsters on his trail. They're bright. They're fast. They're werewolves - and they're catching up. Sam Vimes is out of time, out of luck and already out of breath...", "imageUrl": "https://images-na.ssl-images-amazon.com/images/S/compressed.photo.goodreads.com/books/1327961702i/63720.jpg", "genres": ["Novels", "Science Fiction Fantasy", "Comedy", "Fantasy", "Audiobook", "Mystery", "High Fantasy", "Humor", "Fiction", "Adventure"], "asin": "0552154229", "isbn": "0552154229", "isbn13": "9780552154222", "publisher": "Corgi", "series": ["Discworld - Ankh-Morpork City Watch", "Kolekcja \u015awiat Dysku", "Discworld"], "author": ["Terry Pratchett"], "publishDate": 1231228800000, "characters": ["Wolfgang von \u00dcberwald", "Sam Vimes", "Havelock Vetinari", "Carrot Ironfoundersson", "Sybil Deidre Olgivanna Ramkin", "Gaspode", "Cheery Littlebottom", "Nobby Nobbs", "DEATH", "Fred Colon", "Angua von \u00dcberwald", "Igor (Discworld)"], "places": ["\u00dcberwald"], "ratingHistogram": [459, 1134, 9332, 27013, 34704], "ratingsCount": 72642, "reviewsCount": 2006, "numPages": 464, "language": "English", "awards": [{"name": "Locus Award", "awardedAt": 946713600000, "category": "Fantasy", "hasWon": null}]}
{"url": "https://www.goodreads.com/book/show/103983.Skeleton_Key", "title": "Skeleton Key", "titleComplete": "Skeleton Key (Alex Rider, #3)", "description": "Alex Rider is now an IMDb TV/Amazon Original Series!Alex Rider is an orphan turned teen superspy who's saving the world one mission at a time\u2014from #1 New York Times bestselling author!Alex Rider has been through a lot for his fourteen years. He's been shot at by international terrorists, chased down a mountainside on a makeshift snowboard, and has stood face-to-face with pure evil. Twice, young Alex has managed to save the world. And twice, he has almost been killed doing it. But now Alex faces something even more dangerous. The desperation of a man who has lost everything he cared his country and his only son. A man who just happens to have a nuclear weapon and a serious grudge against the free world. To see his beloved Russia once again be a dominant power, he will stop at nothing. Unless Alex can stop him first... Uniting forces with America's own CIA for the first time, teen spy Alex Rider battles terror from the sun-baked beaches of Miami all the way to the barren ice fields of northernmost Russia.From the author of Magpie Murders and Moriarty .", "imageUrl": "https://images-na.ssl-images-amazon.com/images/S/compressed.photo.goodreads.com/books/1306076661i/103983.jpg", "genres": ["Middle Grade", "Childrens", "Action", "Young Adult", "Mystery", "Teen", "Espionage", "Thriller", "Fiction", "Adventure"], "asin": "0142406147", "isbn": "0142406147", "isbn13": "9780142406144", "publisher": "Puffin Books", "series": ["Alex Rider"], "author": ["Anthony Horowitz"], "publishDate": 1140076800000, "characters": ["Smithers", "Alex Rider", "Alan Blunt", "Mrs Jones", "Sabina Pleasure", "Jack Starbright"], "places": ["Cuba", "Miami, Florida", "Wimbledon, England", "Florida", "Eastern Europe", "Russia"], "ratingHistogram": [437, 2012, 11853, 20149, 21153], "ratingsCount": 55604, "reviewsCount": 1711, "numPages": 327, "