{"url": "https://www.goodreads.com/book/show/34502.Soul_Music", "title": "Soul Music", "titleComplete": "Soul Music (Discworld, #16; Death, #3)", "description": "Other children get given xylophones. Susan just had to ask her grandfather to take his vest off. Yes. There's a Death in the family.It's hard to grow up normally when Grandfather rides a white horse and wields a scythe \u2013 especially when you have to take over the family business, and everyone mistakes you for the Tooth Fairy.And especially when you have to face the new and addictive music that has entered Discworld.It's lawless. It changes people.It's called \"Music With Rocks In.\"It's got a beat and you can dance to it, but...It's ALIVE.And it won't fade away.", "imageUrl": "https://images-na.ssl-images-amazon.com/images/S/compressed.photo.goodreads.com/books/1168566175i/34502.jpg", "genres": ["Science Fiction Fantasy", "Comedy", "Fantasy", "Audiobook", "Magic", "Death", "Music", "High Fantasy", "Humor", "Fiction"], "asin": "057506689X", "isbn": "057506689X", "isbn13": "9780575066892", "publisher": "Gollancz", "series": ["Kolekcja \u015awiat Dysku", "Death", "Discworld"], "author": ["Terry Pratchett"], "publishDate": 915177600000, "characters": ["Cut Me Own Throat Dibbler", "Havelock Vetinari", "Death of Rats", "Foul Ole Ron", "DEATH", "The Librarian", "Susan Sto Helit"], "ratingHistogram": [570, 2749, 16933, 30385, 28236], "ratingsCount": 78873, "reviewsCount": 2521, "numPages": 288, "language": "English"}
{"url": "https://www.goodreads.com/book/show/6882.Papillon", "title": "Papillon", "titleComplete": "Papillon", "description": "Henri Charri\u00e8re, called \"Papillon,\" for the butterfly tattoo on his chest, was convicted in Paris in 1931 of a murder he did not commit. Sentenced to life imprisonment in the penal colony of French Guiana, he became obsessed with one goal: escape. After planning and executing a series of treacherous yet failed attempts over many years, he was eventually sent to the notorious prison, Devil's Island, a place from which no one had ever escaped . . . until Papillon. His flight to freedom remains one of the most incredible feats of human cunning, will, and endurance ever undertaken.Charri\u00e8re's astonishing autobiography, Papillon, was published in France to instant acclaim in 1968, more than twenty years after his final escape. Since then, it has become a treasured classic -- the gripping, shocking, ultimately uplifting odyssey of an innocent man who simply would not be defeated.", "imageUrl": "https://images-na.ssl-images-amazon.com/images/S/compressed.photo.goodreads.com/books/1327865561i/6882.jpg", "genres": ["Classics", "Memoir", "France", "History", "Nonfiction", "Crime", "Biography", "Autobiography", "Adventure", "Biography Memoir"], "asin": "0061120669", "isbn": "0061120669", "isbn13": "9780061120664", "publisher": "William Morrow Paperbacks", "series": ["Papillon"], "author": ["Henri Charri\u00e8re"], "publishDate": 1154415600000, "places": ["Devil's Island", "French Guiana", "France", "Paris"], "ratingHistogram": [829, 2123, 9590, 24751, 32228], "ratingsCount": 69521, "reviewsCount": 2819, "numPages": 544, "language": "English"}
