{"url": "https://www.goodreads.com/book/show/11566.The_Green_Mile", "title": "The Green Mile", "titleComplete": "The Green Mile", "description": "At Cold Mountain Penitentiary, along the lonely stretch of cells known as the Green Mile, condemned killers such as 'Billy the Kid' Wharton and the possessed Eduard Delacroix await death strapped in 'Old Sparky'. But good or evil, innocent or guilty, prisoner or guard, none has ever seen the brutal likes of the new prisoner, John Coffey, sentenced to death for raping and murdering two young girls. Is Coffey a devil in human form? Or is he a far, far different kind of being?There are more wonders in heaven and hell than anyone at Cold Mountain can imagine and one of those wonders might just have stepped in amongst them.", "imageUrl": "https://images-na.ssl-images-amazon.com/images/S/compressed.photo.goodreads.com/books/1373903563i/11566.jpg", "genres": ["Classics", "Supernatural", "Fantasy", "Paranormal", "Crime", "Mystery", "Historical Fiction", "Horror", "Thriller", "Fiction"], "asin": "0451933028", "isbn": "0451933028", "isbn13": "9780451933027", "publisher": "Penguin Signet", "series": ["The Green Mile"], "author": ["Stephen King"], "publishDate": 843721200000, "characters": ["John Coffey", "Brutus Howell", "Paul Edgecomb", "Percy Wetmore", "American Law Enforcement"], "places": ["Louisiana, United States"], "ratingHistogram": [1311, 4363, 27593, 93115, 191487], "ratingsCount": 317869, "reviewsCount": 12631, "numPages": 592, "language": "English", "awards": [{"name": "Bram Stoker Award", "awardedAt": 820483200000, "category": "Best Novel", "hasWon": null}, {"name": "Audie Award", "awardedAt": 852105600000, "category": "Fiction, Unabridged", "hasWon": null}]}
{"url": "https://www.goodreads.com/book/show/285092.High_Fidelity", "title": "High Fidelity", "titleComplete": "High Fidelity", "description": "Do you know your desert-island, all-time, top five most memorable split-ups?Rob does. He keeps a list, in fact. But Laura isn't on it - even though she's just become his latest ex. He's got his life back, you see. He can just do what he wants when he wants: like listen to whatever music he likes, look up the girls that are on his list, and generally behaves as if Laura never mattered. But Rob finds he can't move on. He's stuck in a really deep groove - and it's called Laura. Soon, Rob's asking himself some big questions: about love, about life - and about why we choose to share ours with the people we do.", "imageUrl": "https://images-na.ssl-images-amazon.com/images/S/compressed.photo.goodreads.com/books/1327928082i/285092.jpg", "genres": ["Contemporary", "Novels", "Comedy", "Literature", "Music", "Adult Fiction", "Humor", "Fiction", "Romance", "British Literature"], "asin": "1573225517", "isbn": "1573225517", "isbn13": "9781573225519", "publisher": "Riverhead Books", "author": ["Nick Hornby"], "publishDate": 831279600000, "characters": ["Rob Gordon"], "places": ["London, England"], "ratingHistogram": [2738, 10452, 46680, 83002, 57744], "ratingsCount": 200616, "reviewsCount": 7941, "numPages": 323, "language": "English"}
