{"url": "https://www.goodreads.com/book/show/5297.The_Picture_of_Dorian_Gray", "title": "The Picture of Dorian Gray", "titleComplete": "The Picture of Dorian Gray", "description": "Oscar Wilde\u2019s only novel is the dreamlike story of a young man who sells his soul for eternal youth and beauty.In this celebrated work Wilde forged a devastating portrait of the effects of evil and debauchery on a young aesthete in late-19th-century England. Combining elements of the Gothic horror novel and decadent French fiction, the book centers on a striking premise: As Dorian Gray sinks into a life of crime and gross sensuality, his body retains perfect youth and vigor while his recently painted portrait grows day by day into a hideous record of evil, which he must keep hidden from the world. For over a century, this mesmerizing tale of horror and suspense has enjoyed wide popularity. It ranks as one of Wilde's most important creations and among the classic achievements of its kind.", "imageUrl": "https://images-na.ssl-images-amazon.com/images/S/compressed.photo.goodreads.com/books/1546103428i/5297.jpg", "genres": ["Classics", "Novels", "Fantasy", "Audiobook", "Literature", "19th Century", "Gothic", "Horror", "LGBT", "Fiction"], "publisher": "Random House: Modern Library", "author": ["Oscar Wilde", "Jeffrey Eugenides"], "publishDate": 1086073200000, "characters": ["Lady Victoria Wotton", "Alan Campbell", "Adrian Singleton", "Lord Staveley", "Basil Hallward", "Sibyl Vane", "Henry Ashton", "Lady Narborough", "James Vane", "Lady Gwendolen", "Lord Henry Wotton", "Duchess of Monmouth", "Dorian Gray"], "places": ["London, England", "England"], "ratingHistogram": [19756, 59810, 259606, 551574, 627024], "ratingsCount": 1517770, "reviewsCount": 68555, "numPages": 272, "language": "English"}
{"url": "https://www.goodreads.com/book/show/511533.The_Dare_Game", "title": "The Dare Game", "titleComplete": "The Dare Game (Tracy Beaker, #2)", "description": "I'M TRACY BEAKER, THE GREAT INVENTOR OF EXTREMELY OUTRAGEOUS DARES - AND I DARE YOU TO READ A MORE BRILLIANT STORY THAN THIS!I've bought a big fat purple notebook for writing down all my mega-manic ultra-scary stories in. But especially for my own story. Of how my foster-mum, Cam, has turned out to be a real meanie. No designer clothes, when I really need them. A pokey flat, and a horrible new school. No wonder I bunk off . . . Still, it will have to do until my real mum comes and gets me. And until then, no-one is going to be better at the Dare Game than Tracy Beaker!", "imageUrl": "https://images-na.ssl-images-amazon.com/images/S/compressed.photo.goodreads.com/books/1320505713i/511533.jpg", "genres": ["Contemporary", "Middle Grade", "Childrens", "Novels", "Comedy", "Young Adult", "Humor", "Teen", "Fiction", "Realistic Fiction"], "asin": "0440867584", "isbn": "0440867584", "isbn13": "9780440867586", "publisher": "Corgi", "series": ["Tracy Beaker"], "author": ["Jacqueline Wilson"], "publishDate": 1161673200000, "characters": ["Tracy Beaker"], "ratingHistogram": [152, 723, 2100, 1563, 1200], "ratingsCount": 5738, "reviewsCount": 189, "numPages": 256}
