{"url": "https://www.goodreads.com/book/show/540020.The_Day_of_the_Jackal", "title": "The Day of the Jackal", "titleComplete": "The Day of the Jackal", "description": "Librarian note: an alternate cover for this edition can be found here.The Jackal. A tall, blond Englishman with opaque, gray eyes. A killer at the top of his profession. A man unknown to any secret service in the\u00a0 world. An assassin with a contract to kill the world's most heavily guarded man.One\u00a0 man with a rifle who can change the course of history. One man whose mission is so secretive not\u00a0even his employers know his name. And as the\u00a0minutes count down to the final act of execution, it\u00a0seems that there is no power on earth that can stop\u00a0the Jackal.", "imageUrl": "https://images-na.ssl-images-amazon.com/images/S/compressed.photo.goodreads.com/books/1405364996i/540020.jpg", "genres": ["Classics", "Novels", "Crime", "Mystery", "Suspense", "Historical Fiction", "Mystery Thriller", "Espionage", "Thriller", "Fiction"], "asin": "0553266306", "publisher": "Bantam", "author": ["Frederick Forsyth"], "publishDate": 305017200000, "characters": ["the Jackal", "Jacqueline Dumas", "Victor Kowalski", "Claude Lebel", "Roger Frey", "Charles de Gaulle"], "places": ["France", "Paris"], "ratingHistogram": [1197, 2809, 17693, 49347, 62877], "ratingsCount": 133923, "reviewsCount": 2687, "numPages": 358, "language": "English", "awards": [{"name": "Martin Beck Award", "awardedAt": 63100800000, "category": null, "hasWon": null}, {"name": "Edgar Award", "awardedAt": 63100800000, "category": "Best Novel", "hasWon": null}]}
